column8: Out of order IP fragmentation : a fragment with a size less than 9 bytes (allowed but could be an evasion).
Overlapping unordered IP fragmentation : difference in offset of concomitant fragments less than fragment length (allowed but could be an evasion).
The minimum size of an IP fragment is 28 bytes and for an IP fragment with offset 0 it is 40.
